Ž:Y<?php exit; ?>a:6:{s:10:"last_error";s:0:"";s:10:"last_query";s:62:"SELECT wp_posts.* FROM wp_posts WHERE ID IN (1099,990,594,591)";s:11:"last_result";a:4:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"591";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2017-04-07 12:08:02";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2017-04-07 12:08:02";s:12:"post_content";s:1419:"[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]You woke up this morning, and suddenly, you notice a blister on your lips. You think it will go away by itself, but then, other symptoms start to develop. You experience itching and a burning sensation in the mouth, and have trouble eating as your mouth has become extra sensitive. These are all symptoms of a cold sore.

A cold sore is also referred to as a fever blister, where you get or develop small lesions that look like blisters or very small sores inside your mouth or on the face (<a href="https://shcs.ucdavis.edu/topics/cold-sores" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">1</a>). These sores or lesions can appear on the cheeks, chin, inside the nose, in your nostrils, lips, sometimes on the gums and, in a few cases, also on the palate. These are caused by the Herpes Simplex virus (2). The cold sore virus is highly contagious and spreads by contact with an infected person.

You now know that you have a cold sore, and your doctor has established the fact for you as well. The problem is none of you would like to have that ugly looking sore or lesion spoil your evening or an important meeting that you have lined up for yourself. Well, there are always simple and easy ways to get rid of it. Keep reading to find out how.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_widget_sidebar sidebar_id="healthy_nutrition___food_sidebar"][/vc_column][/vc_row]";s:10:"post_title";s:43:"18 Ways To Get Rid Of A Cold Sore Overnight";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:43:"18-ways-to-get-rid-of-a-cold-sore-overnight";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2017-04-20 12:07:15";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2017-04-20 12:07:15";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:41:"http://localhost/homemadesolutions/?p=591";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:1;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"594";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2017-04-07 12:12:01";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2017-04-07 12:12:01";s:12:"post_content";s:993:"[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]Itâ€™s that time of the month, and you are already dreading the pain, the cramps, and the hassle of changing your sanitary napkins (or tampons) a couple of hundred times. Alright, alright, I might have exaggerated a bit. But thatâ€™s how it feels, doesnâ€™t it? To add to this, when you have an important event lined up around this time, all you need is a magic pill to stop your periods earlier than usual.

You donâ€™t have to run from pillar to post for a solution. Simple ingredients that are found in your house can help to stop your period early or even postpone them. It is important to understand that once your menses have started, there is no way to stop them completely. However, many of the home remedies listed below can postpone them and even reduce the flow by relaxing your uterine muscles.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_widget_sidebar sidebar_id="healthy_nutrition___food_sidebar"][/vc_column][/vc_row]";s:10:"post_title";s:29:"How To Stop Your Period Early";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:29:"how-to-stop-your-period-early";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2017-04-20 12:06:56";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2017-04-20 12:06:56";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:41:"http://localhost/homemadesolutions/?p=594";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:2;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"990";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"2";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2017-05-02 11:49:03";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2017-05-02 11:49:03";s:12:"post_content";s:4418:"[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]

