<h3>Benefits of Turmeric For Brain Health</h3>
Recently, turmeric's ability to improve brain function was relatively unknown when it was found that active ingredient found in curcumin, Turmeric, could be very helpful in the treatment of Alzheimer's disease. Researchers have found Effects of turmeric on Liver And Brain that 40% of the curcumin can stop the production of one of the primary causes for Alzheimer's, which is beta-amyloid plaques.
curcumin is a powerful anti-inflammatory property which can play a major role in Alzheimerâ€™s treatment as well, as it reduces damage caused by inflammation and oxidizing agents, and turmeric can be used for the treatment of depression.
<h3>Benefits of TurmericÂ Liver and Cancer Prevention</h3>
The fact is that the turmeric has been used for the treatment of diseases of the liver from centuries, but valid scientific research has only been conducted in the last few decades.
Turmeric is very much effective in reduce liver damage caused by ethanol (kind of alcohol), high toxicity levels, liver disease (like cholestasis), cirrhosis (scarring of the liver), and iron overdose.
Turmeric which has curcumin can reduce the risk of liver cancer. It does this by reducing the effects that human carcinogens (like thioacetamide) have on the liver.
